==Old English==

===Etymology===
From Germanic: cognate with Old Frisian ''dēma'', Old Saxon ''dōmian'' (Dutch [[doemen]]), Old High German [[tuomen]], Old Norse [[dœma]], Gothic [[𐌳𐍉𐌼𐌾𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'de:man/

===Verb===
'''dēman''' (weak verb class 1: '''dēmeþ'''/'''dēmþ''' ‘he judges’; '''dēmaþ''' ‘they judge’; '''dēmde''' ‘he judged’; '''dēmdon''' ‘they judged’; '''ġedēmed''' past participle)
# to [[judge]]

